 Automation Platform MVP
Prerequisites
Basic understanding of Python programming
Familiarity with REST APIs and HTTP methods
Knowledge of Linux command-line operations
Understanding of background task processing concepts
Basic experience with JSON data structures
Learning Objectives
By completing this lab, you will:

Build an end-to-end automation platform with CLI, API, and worker components
Implement policy-based task execution and validation
Integrate multiple system components into a cohesive automation solution
Create a functional MVP for task automation and orchestration
Environment Setup
Your Linux machine is provided via the "Start Lab" button. You'll install all required tools during this lab.

Install Required Software
# Update system packages
sudo apt update

# Install Python 3 and pip
sudo apt install -y python3 python3-pip python3-venv

# Install Redis (message broker)
sudo apt install -y redis-server

# Start Redis service
sudo systemctl start redis-server
sudo systemctl enable redis-server

# Verify Redis is running
redis-cli ping
# Should return: PONG
Create Project Structure
# Create project directory
mkdir -p ~/automation-platform
cd ~/automation-platform

# Create virtual environment
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate

# Install Python dependencies
pip install flask redis celery click pyyaml
Setup Directory Structure
# Create necessary directories
mkdir -p {api,cli,workers,policies,logs}

# Create configuration file
cat > config.yaml << 'EOF'
redis:
  host: localhost
  port: 6379
  db: 0

api:
  host: 0.0.0.0
  port: 5000

workers:
  concurrency: 2

policies:
  max_retries: 3
  timeout: 300
EOF
